redominantly old and passive at z=0, while lower mass galaxies assemble\nlater and, for M<10^9.5 (Msun), are still predominantly blue and star forming\nat z=0. This phenomenological but physically based model allows the\nobservations to be interpreted in terms of the efficiency of the various\nprocesses that control the formation and evolution of galaxies as a function of\ntheir stellar mass, gas content, environment and time.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Oct 2014 20:00:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 19 Nov 2015 21:00:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-23"}
